         <div type="translation">
            <ab>The never-to-be-forgotten benefactor, who, with baths and with command of the corn-supply, drove away plague and famine, Rhodopaios, lover of his country; the city, loving him, has adorned him with this second <material key="marmor">marble</material> image, repaying him with worthy honours.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>For Rhodopaios, see <ref type="inscription" n="85" target="050016.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="87" target="110515.xml"/>, and discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="VI.26" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
